And now for the grand finale! Keep
your eyes peeledâ€”you won't want to
miss a second of the action!
8:
"The Mystery Beauty of Paradise Isle:
Shining Eclair!"
10:
"In mere days, she's taken the island
by storm. Local businesses are
jumping at the chance to hire this
dazzling performer!"
13:
Let's see... So far she's performed at
the casino, modeled for the spa and
beach hut, joined a swimming
contest, and... given this show, right?
16:
"But just who is this star that burns
brighter than the sun? Who is
Shining Eclair?!"
19:
I see you're already writing your
article. I can't wait to read the
finished product.
23:
Your show was amazing... But aren't
you tired?
27:
Not at all. In fact, I was just
wondering what I should do next.
30:
Just who are you, Eclair? How can
you have so much energy?
33:
I belong to a fighting troupe called
the Platinum Legends back home. 
In fact, I'm the champion there.
36:
Alk and Stella here are actually
creating promotional material for
that very troupe.
40:
Ah, I'm sorry. I suppose we should
have explained this sooner.
44:
I mean, it's not like you had the
time... You've been running around
all day.
47:
No matter what they're asking of
you, you always just smile and
agree. It's a bad habit of yours.
51:
Is it though? I'm just glad they're
choosing to ask me of all people.
Why wouldn't I say yes?
57:
I'm sorry that it's cut into our
interview time though.
60:
Why don't we head back to the hotel
and get started?
63:
A-are you sure? I'd hate to interrupt
your rest...
66:
It's fine. Ask as many questions as
you like.
70:
I'm gonna look through the pictures
we took today. Think you can handle
an interview, Stella?
80:
Then it's settled. I am in your hands,
my dear interviewers.
87:
"You've been the undefeated champ
for a long time. What is your secret?"
91:
Diligence. I take every part of my
day seriously, from my training to
my meals and time off...
95:
And of course, my desire to win.
Without those two things, I would
certainly have fallen by now.
98:
Gina, what about you? Feel free to
ask whatever you like.
101:
Th-thank you! Let's see... 
Are you enjoying your time on 
Paradise Isle?
104:
That I am. The scenery is
breathtaking, and there's plenty of
things to do. It's the perfect vacation
spot.
107:
I'm sure the tourism department will
be happy to hear that.
109:
You normally work as a coliseum
fighter, correct? How did you get
started?
112:
Well... I was scouted after someone
saw my skills with the sword.
115:
Fighting suits me well enough, and
the fans can't get enough of Shining
Eclair.
121:
If you hadn't joined the coliseum,
what do you think you'd be doing
now?
124:
...Is that question meant for this
interview?
128:
...No. My apologies. I suppose it's just
something I was personally
interested in.
130:
There was a time when I aimed to
be a performer here on Paradise
Isle. But... I didn't have the talent.
133:
That must be when you got into
your current line of work.
136:
That's right... But occasionally I
wonder what would've happened if I
hadn't given up.
138:
I suppose I got a little jealous
hearing about your own resolve and
success...
141:
...I'm sorry. I don't know if I can give
you an answer right this second...
144:
N-no, it's my fault for asking
something unexpected! Anyway, it's
getting late, so I'll head out!
147:
Gina, thank you for telling me about
your past.
151:
I promise I will come up with an
answer to your question. Now then,
see you tomorrow.
161:
Just for a little while longer. Do you
think Alk could join us?
171:
No matter how hard I think about it, I
just can't imagine what my life
would be like without the coliseum.
179:
I've been Shining Eclair for a long
time now. That's what the fans want
from me, so that's what I give them.
182:
I suppose I am a little curious. Who
would I be if I wasn't Shining Eclair?
186:
Hehe, the moonlight has a strange
way of compelling you to reflect,
doesn't it?
191: Do you regret joining the coliseum?
195:
...No. That's why it's such a
perplexing question.
199:
The Platinum Legends have allowed
me to bring joy to others. I even met
you two through the coliseum. 
How could I regret that?
202:
I think that's enough for today's
interview. Thank you.
207:
We should be thanking you. You
basically just gave us an exclusive
scoop.
211: The nights are so beautiful here.
215: I'm glad I came here with you two...
